flammation and fibrosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pneumoconiosis","Bronchiectasis","Pulmonary oedema","Chronic bronchitis","Emphysema"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPneumoconiosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a chronic interstitial lung disease caused by long-term inhalation of dust particles (e.g., coal, silica, asbestos). It leads to inflammation, fibrosis and stiffening of the lung parenchyma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBronchiectasis\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by abnormal dilation of airways, not interstitial disease. \u003Cstrong\u003EPulmonary oedema\u003C/strong\u003E causes acute fluid accumulation in the alveoli rather than chronic fibrosis. \u003Cstrong\u003EChronic bronchitis\u003C/strong\u003E is an airway disease with mucus hypersecretion. \u003Cstrong\u003EEmphysema\u003C/strong\u003E involves destruction of alveolar walls leading to increased lung compliance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe stiff lungs in pneumoconiosis result from progressive scarring and fibrosis of the lung tissue, leading to a restrictive pattern on pulmonary function tests.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Pneumoconiosis is a chronic interstitial lung disease caused by inhaled dust particles that leads to inflammation and fibrosis.","Interstitial lung diseases cause reduced lung compliance through scarring of the lung parenchyma.","Restrictive lung diseases can be caused by intrinsic lung pathology (like pneumoconiosis) or extrinsic factors (like obesity)."],"references":["Zosky GR, Hoy RF, Silverstone EJ, Brims FJ, Miles S, Johnson AR, Gibson PG, Yates DH. Coal workers\u0027 pneumoconiosis: an Australian perspective. Med J Aust. 2016 Jun 20;204(11):414-8. doi: 10.5694/mja16.00357. PMID: 27318401.","Qi XM, Luo Y, Song MY, Liu Y, Shu T, Liu Y, Pang JL, Wang J, Wang C. Pneumoconiosis: current status and future prospects. Chin Med J (Engl). 2021 Apr 13;134(8):898-907. doi: 10.1097/CM9.0000000000001461. PMID: 33879753; PMCID: PMC8078400.","Mason, R. J., Broaddus, V. C., Martin, T. R., King, T. E., Schraufnagel, D., Murray, J. F., \u0026 Nadel, J. A. (2010). Murray and Nadel\u0027s textbook of respiratory medicine E-book: 2-volume set. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98252"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15471"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98252","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98252"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-27T21:00:47+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-27T21:01:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8162"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116257"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"h